==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[affiliatio]]'', noun of action from verb ''[[affiliare]]'', '''affiliate''', from ''[[aff-]]'', combining form of ''[[ad]]'', '''to''', + ''[[filiare]]'', verb formed from ''[[filius]]'', '''son'''

===Noun===
'''affiliation'''

# The relationship resulting from [[affiliate|affiliating]] one thing with another.
# A [[club]], [[society]] or [[umbrella organisation]] so formed, esp. a [[trade union]].

